OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FCouncils across Wales are considering
OL,7,Fwhether to introduce a tourism tax,
OL,8,Fwith the proposal dividing opinion
OL,9,Famong businesses, residents and
OL,10,Fvisitors.
OL,12,FFrom 2027, local authorities will have
OL,13,Fthe power to charge visitors an
OL,14,Fadditional fee for overnight stays in
OL,15,Ftourist accommodation.
OL,17,FThe Welsh Government says the money
OL,18,Fraised will be reinvested into local
OL,19,Fservices and infrastructure to help
OL,20,Fcommunities cope with the pressures
OL,21,Fcreated by tourism.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
