PN,43702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FHowever, some in the tourism industry
OL,7,Ffear the tax could make parts of Wales
OL,8,Fless appealing as a holiday
OL,9,Fdestination.
OL,11,FVisitors staying in hotels, bed and
OL,12,Fbreakfasts, self-catering
OL,13,Faccommodation and holiday caravans
OL,14,Fwould pay #1.30 per person, per night,
OL,15,Fplus VAT, where councils choose to
OL,16,Fintroduce the levy. Guests staying in
OL,17,Fhostels and campsites would pay 80p
OL,18,Fper person, per night, plus VAT.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
