FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FBedwyr ap Gwyn, who runs outdoor
OL,7,Factivities company Pellennig, says
OL,8,Ftourism is vital to the local economy
OL,9,Fbut comes at a cost for those who live
OL,10,Fthere.
OL,12,F"The impact on local people, traffic
OL,13,Fand parking can be very challenging,"
OL,14,Fhe said.
OL,16,FDuring busy summer weekends, roads
OL,17,Fbecome congested, car parks fill up
OL,18,Fand some of the area's most popular
OL,19,Fbeauty spots experience litter
OL,20,Fproblems.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FMr ap Gwyn supports the introduction
OL,7,Fof a tourism tax, saying similar
OL,8,Fschemes already operate successfully
OL,9,Facross many European destinations.
OL,11,F"It's a very small amount of money.
OL,12,FI've paid tourism taxes in other
OL,13,Fcountries for years and I can't see it
OL,14,Fstopping people from coming to Wales.
OL,16,F"If it's spent properly for the
OL,17,Fbenefit of the local community, which
OL,18,Fin turn benefits tourism, I honestly
OL,19,Fcan't see a downside."
OL,21,FBusinesses Fear Added Costs
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FHowever not everyone agrees.
OL,8,FGeraint Rowlands, who runs a caravan
OL,9,Fpark near Dolgellau, believes many
OL,10,Ftourism businesses are already under
OL,11,Ffinancial pressure.
OL,13,F"The cost of living is already
OL,14,Fsqueezing people," he said.
OL,16,F"A caravan holiday is one of the more
OL,17,Faffordable options available. For some
OL,18,Ffamilies, it's all they can afford, so
OL,19,Fit feels unfair that this tax will
OL,20,Faffect those people."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FHe also questions whether the levy
OL,7,Fwill solve the problems it is intended
OL,8,Fto address.
OL,10,F"I don't think it will fix the issues
OL,11,Fwe already have. The traffic, the
OL,12,Fparking and the lack of public toilets
OL,13,Fwill still be there. If anything, it
OL,14,Fcould make things worse.
OL,16,F"People from places like Manchester,
OL,17,FLiverpool or Birmingham might decide
OL,18,Fjust to come for the day instead of
OL,19,Fstaying overnight. That could mean
OL,20,Feven more traffic and more litter."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FMr Rowlands is also concerned that
OL,7,Fdifferent approaches between
OL,8,Fneighbouring councils could put
OL,9,Fbusinesses at a disadvantage.
OL,11,F"If Gwynedd introduces it but Powys or
OL,12,FDenbighshire doesn't, people may
OL,13,Fsimply choose to stay across the
OL,14,Fborder instead.
OL,16,F"If it was introduced nationally, at
OL,17,Fleast there would be a level playing
OL,18,Ffield.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,F"In principle it sounds great, but
OL,7,Fwe're still unclear about how it will
OL,8,Fwork day-to-day, particularly the
OL,9,Fextra administration businesses will
OL,10,Fhave to deal with."
OL,12,FSimilar concerns were raised by
OL,13,Fbusiness owners during a recent public
OL,14,Fconsultation held by Gwynedd Council
OL,15,Fin Criccieth, where some said bookings
OL,16,Fare already lower and warned the tax
OL,17,Fcould reduce demand further.
OL,19,FEconomic Benefits
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
