PN,43711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government estimates that a
OL,7,Ftourism levy could raise around #30
OL,8,Fmillion a year if every local
OL,9,Fauthority in Wales adopted the scheme.
OL,11,FResearch involving more than 650
OL,12,Fvisitors to Gwynedd found that around
OL,13,Ftwo-thirds said a #1.30 nightly charge
OL,14,Fwould not change their holiday plans.
OL,15,FAround one-third said the extra cost
OL,16,Fcould influence their decision.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FDr ap Gwilym said the additional
OL,7,Fincome could help improve tourism
OL,8,Finfrastructure, maintain public
OL,9,Ffacilities and support local culture
OL,10,Fand heritage.
OL,12,FMany visitors spoken to in Abersoch
OL,13,Fwere supportive of the proposal.
OL,15,F"#1.30 a night isn't much, and if it
OL,16,Fhelps the community we'd be happy to
OL,17,Fpay it," one visitor said.
OL,19,FAnother added: "If the money goes back
OL,20,Finto the community and helps Abersoch,
OL,21,Fwhich we love, we'd happily pay it."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
