PN,43713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FWhat Happens Next?
OL,8,FIf councils decide to introduce the
OL,9,Ftourism levy, visitors will begin
OL,10,Fpaying the charge from 2027 onwards.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for Gwynedd Council
OL,13,Fsaid no decision has yet been made and
OL,14,Fencouraged residents, businesses and
OL,15,Fvisitors to take part in the public
OL,16,Fconsultation before elected members
OL,17,Fmake a decision later this autumn.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1783675170
OL,3,CSupport and concern as councils
OL,4,Cconsider visitor levy
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government said it is a
OL,7,Flegal requirement that revenue from
OL,8,Fthe levy must be spent on tourism
OL,9,Frelated infrastructure and services
OL,10,Fthat help make Wales a world-class
OL,11,Fdestination.
OL,13,F"Local Authorities must report on an
OL,14,Fannual basis how they have used
OL,15,Fvisitor levy revenues, outlining what
OL,16,Fprojects and activity has been funded."
OL,18,FWatch Y Byd ar Bedwar: Croeso am dal?
OL,19,Fon S4C on Monday at 8:00pm. Also
OL,20,Favailable to watch now on S4C Clic,
OL,21,FBBC iPlayer and YouTube.
